   However, poly_chop_def uses CONS, not SNOC, so we need to use induction.

   By induction on p.
   Base: [] <> |0| /\ (chop [] = []) <=> lead [] <> #0
      LHS = F since |0| = []         by poly_zero
      RHS = F since lead [] = #0     by poly_lead_of_zero
   Step: p <> |0| /\ (chop p = p) <=> lead p <> #0 ==>
         !h. h::p <> |0| /\ (chop (h::p) = h::p) <=> lead (h::p) <> #0
